				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Although I don't play AS anymore, I do remember that fluffing used to be a problem. Well, the only real purpose of fluffing is to fluff up to the power of other fluffed people. Well, I think fluffing should be taken out all together (I thought of this back when I still played.) This could be done by making it possible to gain power by ships only by fleeting them. This would eliminate the possiblilty of fluffing, cuz most people are gonna go through the trouble of fleeting hundreds of gunboats or frigates (not to mention they probably wouldn't have enough commanders. This is just a suggestion. For all I know, the devs may not be able to do this, I don't know.<br />_________________<br />~Paradox
<br />
~Christian Debator
<br />
~Enemy of Mod
<br />
~Satan of Archspace</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
