			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">MY 2 CENTS:
<br />

<br />
-fluffing is important in catching the top councils while they are fluffed up, and expeically when they log off...they are easier to kill once you defleet them...
<br />

<br />
IN MY OPINION:
<br />
-put the ship power values back to where they used to be...as we saw this set, the supercouncils (VH then AGOD) were able to outfluff ANYONE...this meant that they could fluff a few mil in a couple turns with their insane production, and even us guys at 800k real power had trouble fluffing more then 100-200k per turn.....by making the ship power what they used to be, the lower guys can fluff considerably quicker, and be able to catch the bigger guys who sit at a few mil power
<br />

<br />
INSTEAD OF MAKING SHIPS WORTH LESS POWER, MAKE A CAP ON HOW HIGH YOUW POWER CAN FLUFF UP. i.e: say you can only fluff 3-4 mil AT MOST......this means that someone at true power 1 mil, could only fluff to 4-5 mil.......and someone at 200k could fluff to 3-4 mil...this means that the big supercouncil players cannot fluff to get away from anyone with their superior production, and since they get capped at how high they can go, people who are smaller can eventually get in range....this also allows, say, a 200ker to fluff and hit 1 mil power players, or evento fluff above a 150ker who may try and hit them when their fleets are out....obviously, if a guy had 4 mil real power, he could still fluff to 7-8 mil, and some smaller guys would not be able to get him
<br />

<br />
the prob with the new changes is still that those with the superior production can fluff too high/fast for anyone to catch them<br />_________________<br />Houston
<br />

<br />

<br />
"If you don't like gay marriage, blame straight people. They're the ones that keep having gay babies."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
