				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">the problem with the new ship points, as seen this past set, is that the biggest/best players still fluff very very fast, while everyone else is now impeded...the supercouncil players were still fluffing million in a short amount of time, whereas the closest person to them was only able to fluff a few hundred k....at least if the ship points/power was reverted back to the old one, everyone would be able to fluff quite quickly, while putting a cap would limit the supercouncil players to be able to fluff indefinitely out of everyones range...ie, people would be able to fluff into their range, since the amount of fluff would be limited, but they also would be able to do it quickly...even if you put a cap now of how much fluff you could have, because the ship power is so small, it would take a long time to fluff into range...the whole point of fluffing up to attack someone is to be able to do it quickly..<br />_________________<br />Houston
